<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-04-16T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-04-16T16:00:00-05:00" n="655" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d655">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">820.7961 Dept. of Commerce Flight/22:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Collier</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-04-16T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">April 16,
                                            1928—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>28. Your telegram No. 50, April 11, 2 p.m. The Department prefers
                                that you avoid any discussion of this subject because it does not
                                desire to indicate even indirectly what this Government’s policy
                                might be in case of eventualities to which you allude. This should
                                not prevent you, however, from rendering assistance to the
                                representatives of American companies to obtain a fair consideration
                                of their propositions.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>